5 Yea, ſo farre of is it, that the laſt and generall iudgement ſhoulde be terrible vnto vs, that it ſhould rather miniſter matter of great ioy and comfort vnto vs. And therefore our Lord and Saviour Ieſus Chriſt having ſet downe the chiefe ſignes and tokens that ſhould go before the day of iudgment, ſaith to the faithful,Luc. 21.28 
                  When yee ſee theſe things begin to come to paſſe, looke vp, and lift vp your heads, for your redemption draweth neere. So that by Chriſtes owne exhortation in this place, when wee thinke vpon the laſt iudgement, we haue cauſe to reioice, not to fear;

to lift vp our heads, not to hang them downe. And that for ſundry reaſons, but I will ſpecifie one or two that are moſt materiall, & fitteſt to cleare this truth.
